sql:
SELECT mc_name 
FROM microcontrollers 
ORDER BY mc_name;

SELECT DISTINCT mc_name
FROM microcontrollers
WHERE obsolete = 0;

SELECT mc_name, description, COUNT(*) OVER () AS total_non_obsolete
FROM microcontrollers
WHERE obsolete = 0;

external_knowledge:
- The term "latest version" refers to the version with the most recent release date for each microcontroller;
- The "package details" include the package name, lead count, and size;
- The "compatibility information" includes the type of compatibility and the ID of the compatible microcontroller;
- The "documents" include the document name, type, and upload date.
